  <thing id="eS2Darklea" name="Darkleaf" description="Similar to leafweave armor (see below), darkleaf armor is made of carefully cured and beautifully carved pieces of darkwood, supplemented by alchemically treated leaves from the darkwood tree.\n\nMaking armor out of darkleaf reduces its arcane spell failure chance by 5% because the armor is so flexible. The maximum Dexterity bonus of darkleaf armor is increased by 1, and armor check penalties are reduced by 2.\n\nDarkleaf heavy armor is treated as medium armor for purposes of movement and other limitations, while darkleaf medium armor is considered to be light armor.\n\nOnly medium and heavy armors normally made of metal can be constructed from darkleaf, and the most common forms are breastplates and banded mail.\n\nCreating darkleaf armor requires a DC25 Craft (alchemy) check in addition to the normal Craft (armorsmithing) checks required to make armor." compset="Material">
    <comment><![CDATA[Trying to give a warning that this can't go on light armor causes issues.  So currently have scripts setup to instead do nothing on Light armor.]]></comment>
    <fieldval field="mtCAHeavy" value="3000"/>
    <fieldval field="mtCAMedium" value="2250"/>
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatArmOK"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatShldOK"/>
    <tag group="EquipType" tag="NotMetal"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="MatRqMetal"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="10000" index="2"><![CDATA[
~ If we are disabled do nothing
doneif (container.parent.tagis[Helper.SpcDisable] <> 0)

container.parent.field[arArcFail].value -= 5
container.parent.field[arMaxDex].value += 1
container.parent.field[arArmorChk].value += 2]]></eval>
    <eval phase="First" priority="10000" index="3"><![CDATA[
~ If we are light armor set tag so we don't do anything
If (container.parent.tagis[ArmorClass.Light] = 1) Then
   perform container.parent.assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
Endif]]></eval>
    <eval phase="First" priority="11000"><![CDATA[
~ If we are disabled do nothing
doneif (container.parent.tagis[Helper.SpcDisable] <> 0)

~ If we're armor, change our class if necessary - we become one class
~ lighter.
if (container.parent.tagis[component.BaseArmor] <> 0) then
   if (container.tagis[ArmorClass.Medium] <> 0) then
      perform container.delete[ArmorClass.Medium]
      perform container.assign[ArmorClass.Light]
      perform container.delete[ArmorCateg.Slows]

      ~adding this tag to the armor makes it count as one category worse for
      ~the purpose of proficiency, meaning it requires the same proficiency
      ~it used to.
      perform container.assign[Helper.Prof1Step]
   elseif (container.tagis[ArmorClass.Heavy] <> 0) then
          perform container.delete[ArmorClass.Heavy]
          perform container.assign[ArmorClass.Medium]

          ~adding this tag to the armor makes it count as one category worse for
          ~the purpose of proficiency, meaning it requires the same proficiency
          ~it used to.

          perform container.assign[Helper.Prof1Step]
   endif
endif

~ Add to our custom description if we're armor
if (container.parent.tagis[component.BaseArmor] <> 0) then
   field[mtDesc].text &= " Decreased armor category and penalties."
endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gS2AciFire" name="Acidic Fire" description="This alchemical concoction combines alchemist&apos;s fire with a strong acid. A direct hit with acidic fire deals 1d4 points of acid damage and 1d4 points of fire damage. Every creature within 5 feet of the point where the acidic fire hits takes 1 point of acid damage and 1 point of fire damage from the splash. On the round following a direct hit, the target takes an additional 1d4 points of fire damage; this damage can be avoided in the same way as for alchemist&apos;s fire." compset="Gear">
