  <thing id="gS2HoSyFla" name="Holy Symbol, Flametouched Iron" description="A holy symbol sacred to the Church of the Silver Flame is made from flametouched iron. It allows a character who can channel energy against undead and fiends to treat the DC to resist the damage as one higher than normal.\n\nMined only in Thrane, flametouched iron is rare and considered sacred by the Church of the Silver Flame. When mined, this iron variety has a speckled dark red color, resembling rust, but when it is refi ned, it takes on a shimmering, silvery hue. Adherents of the Church of the Silver Flame believe that flametouched iron carries the particular blessing of their deity, and they use it to make holy symbols, weapons, and armor.\n\n{b}Pathfinder:{/b} Made to work with Channel Energy instead and removed wording about Turn Undead/Censure Fiends." compset="Gear">
