  <thing id="gS2SpShard" name="Spellshard, Wizard&apos;s (Blank)" description="A wizard can mystically imprint spells into an Eberron dragonshard rather than physically writing them into a spellbook. A single spellshard is about the size of a human fi st and holds the equivalent of 20 pages of spells. Imprinting a spell into a spellshard takes 24 hours and requires the wizard to cast {i}arcane mark.{/i} This unusual use of {i}arcane mark{/i} requires a material component of powdered silver worth 10 gp per page. Once this process is complete, the wizard can concentrate on the shard in order to bring any spell stored in it into focus; the spell appears as silvery writing within the swirling colors of the shard.\n\n{b}Pathfinder:{/b} Lowered the cost down to 10gp a page from 100 as Pathfinder made writting new spells much cheaper." compset="Gear">
