  <thing id="S2EctopArm" name="Shard, Ectoplasmic Armor" description="This shard provides the bearer with a +2 armor bonus to AC. When it is active, the bearer&apos;s body is surrounded by a ghostly image of a monstrous quori form. The bonuses from multiple shards stack with one another, to a maximum bonus of +10; however, with every additional shard the ghostly image becomes increasingly visible. The image produced by a single shard is barely noticeable, but the image produced by five shards in conjunction (granting a +10 AC bonus) looks like a solid, real monster.\n\nBecause the armor is composed of stable astral ectoplasm, the armor is treated as a material, physical object without any special qualities other than the armor bonus it provides to AC. Ectoplasmic armor has no armor check penalty and does not reduce the wearer&apos;s speed." compset="Ability" summary="This shard provides the bearer with a +2 armor bonus to AC." uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>This is a helper object that gives +2 AC per shard to a maximum of +10.</comment>
    <fieldval field="actName" value="Ectoplasmic Armor"/>
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Activation"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="PreAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
~ If not activated get out now
doneif (field[abilActive].value <> 1)

~ Count up the number of Ectoplasmic Armor shards we have
field[abValue].value += hero.tagcount[Eberron.ioS2EctArm]

~ We have max value of +10 we can provide
field[abValue2].value = minimum(field[abValue].value * 2, 10)
~ Give AC bonus
#applybonus[tACArmor, hero.child[ArmorClass], field[abValue2].value]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioS2EctoFi" name="Shard, Ectoplasmic Fist" description="This shard must be implanted on the hand, forearm, or foot, and only one {i}ectoplasmic fist shard{/i} can be implanted on any one limb. While active, the shard surrounds the associated limb with a ghostly outline of a quori limb. This effect allows the bearer to make unarmed attacks without provoking attacks of opportunity from armed opponents. In addition, his effective size is increased by one category for the purpose of determining the damage of his unarmed attacks.\n\n{B}Note:{/b} Enter the limb this shard is embedded into into the text box." compset="Wondrous" summary="This shard surrounds the associated limb with a ghostly outline of a quori limb.">
