  <thing id="ioS2EterW0" name="Eternal wand (0-level spell)" description="During the final years of the Last War, the artificers and wizards of House Cannith perfected a new form of wand built around an Eberron shard. An {i}eternal wand{/i} holds an arcane spell of 3rd level or lower with a maximum caster level of 6th. Unlike a traditional wand that holds 50 charges, an {i}eternal wand{/i} allows any character who can cast arcane spells to use the spell contained in it twice per day.\n\nThe development of the {i}eternal wand{/i} allowed magewrights to take the place of war wizards during the final days of the Last War, supplementing their passive spells with more aggressive magic. While the artificers of House Cannith have been searching for ways to streamline the process of creation, the technique is still in its infancy. Currently the wands are rarely seen except in military units, but a few magewrights who served in the war brought their {i}eternal wands of magic missile{/i} home from the front lines." compset="Wondrous" summary="Allows any arcane caster to cast the spell twice per day.">
