  <thing id="ipS2wKeeFa" name="Keeper&apos;s Fang" description="The Keeper is the Sovereign Lord of Death and Decay. He is said to have a vast domain hidden beneath the Demon Wastes, populated by souls that he has snatched away from Dolurrh. A Keeper&apos;s fang weapon has been consecrated to the Lord of Death, and incorporates a Khyber shard into the hilt. If it is used to strike a killing blow, the soul of the victim is trapped in the Keeper&apos;s domain, and the victim cannot be brought back to life using {i}resurrection, raise dead, reincarnate,{/i} or similar effects. But all is not lost - stories tell of heroes who have found the lair of the Keeper and brought the souls of their companions back from bondage.{br}{br}A Keeper&apos;s fang weapon is evil-aligned. The blade or stock of the weapon is engraved with the runes of the Keeper; a successful DC 20 Knowledge (religion) check allows a character to recognize the nature and purpose of the weapon. Most followers of the Sovereign Host consider the mere possession of a Keeper&apos;s fang weapon to be an abominable act; the use of the weapon is a heinous and unforgivable crime.{br}{br}Only melee weapons can be dedicated as Keeper&apos;s fang weapons." compset="ItemPower">
