  <thing id="ipS2wWater" name="Waterborn" description="A waterborn weapon has a Small water elemental bound to it, and takes on a milky blue-white appearance. If the weapon is a slashing or bludgeoning weapon, this property negates the normal penalties for using such a weapon underwater, as if the wielder were under the effect of a {i}freedom of movement{/i} spell. If the weapon is a piercing weapon, this property grants an additional +2 bonus on its wielder&apos;s attack rolls and damage rolls when both the wielder and his opponent are touching water.{br}{br}When the wielder of a waterborn weapon uses it from land to attack a creature in the water, this property negates the cover normally granted to swimming creatures against attacks from land, again as if the wielder were under the effect of {i}freedom of movement.{/i}" compset="ItemPower" summary="Easily use this weapon in water as if under the effect of a {i}freedom of movement{/i} spell.">
